Description of male (
Fig. 1
). Body lustrous including elytra, glabrous (with scarce short setae on apical third of elytra), completely yellowish orange, except apices of mandibles black.

Elytra lustrous, 2.20 times as long as wide and 0.70 times as long as body, with three distinct costae starting on or near humerus and ending before apex and traces of the fourth costa in apical half of elytral length along suture. Apex moderately rounded (
Fig. 12
). Epipleura narrow, disappearing before apex.

Ventral surface subopaque, finely punctate, covered with pale setae. Abdomen simple, last ventrite with subtriangular impression in middle of posterior half, posterior margin with two very small incisions (
Fig. 15
).

Aedeagus symmetrical, wide, apex triangular with moderately rounded tip. In lateral view, apical quarter slightly bent up (
Fig. 7
).

Female (
Fig. 2
, holotype
Fig. 3
). Body brownish, with black metaventrite, sometimes with brownish abdomen. Elytra dull, apex distinctly prolonged (
Fig. 13
). All first tarsomeres not enlarged, elongate. Last ventrite with large semicircular incision, penultimate ventrite with posterior margin strongly beveled (
Fig. 14
). Gonocoxae separated in anterior third, each apical process bearing four setae apically and additional two setae laterally, base semicircular (
Fig. 9
). Spermatheca: cornu shortly C-shaped, without distinct nodulus, proximal spermathecal duct long, gradually narrowed (
Fig. 10
). Sternite VIII oval, anterior margin slightly concave, setae cummulated along anterior margin except one seta laterally, tignum thin, slightly longer than sternite VIII (
Fig. 11
).

Distribution. Thailand (
Medvedev 2000 a, present paper
). New species for Laos and Myanmar .
